name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania v. Jimmy GONZALES, Appellant

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania v. Jimmy GONZALES, Appellant.

opinions.text:
ORDER
Petition for allowance of appeal was granted 11/18/86. Issues raised in that appeal have since been addressed in Com. v. Sojourner and McMillam v. Penna. Petition for Clarification granted and appeal is dismissed as moot.

attorneys: Neil E. Jokelson, Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant.
Ronald Eisenberg, Chief, Appeals, Dist. Attys. Office, Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.
casebody.head_matter:
558 A.2d 529
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania v. Jimmy GONZALES, Appellant.
Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
Dec. 12, 1988.
Neil E. Jokelson, Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant.
Ronald Eisenberg, Chief, Appeals, Dist. Attys. Office, Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.
